最初由学生在1998年由美国国际开发署，国际共和党研究所和美国国家民主基金会资助的学生组成的一个名为Otpor！的团体，是推翻米洛舍维奇的推土机革命的众多重要参与者之一。<ref name="nyt20001126">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/library/magazine/home/20001126mag-serbia.html|title=Who Really Brought Down Milosevic?|access-date=2008-02-08|work=New York Times|date=2000-11-26|first=Roger|last=Cohen|archive-date=2017-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226165528/http://www.nytimes.com/library/magazine/home/20001126mag-serbia.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>美国国际开发署向Otpor捐赠了超过3,000万美元，以“为DOS的领导层购买手机和计算机，并招募和培训2万名选举监督员的军队”，并为他们补充“以海报，徽章和T恤进行的复杂营销活动”。<ref>Gallagher, T., 2005. The Balkans in the New Millennium: In the Shadow of War and Peace. London: Routledge. p.112.</ref>2000年10月5日的推土机革命后，美国在贝尔格莱德重新建立了外交存在。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?language=en&id=1116959|title=KUNA : U.S. AGREES TO REOPEN EMBASSY IN BELGRADE - Politics - 13/10/2000|access-date=2016-05-02|archive-date=2019-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190129181747/https://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?language=en&id=1116959|dead-url=no}}</ref>2013年，美联社发表文章称，美国中央情报局特工弗朗西斯·阿齐布尔德参与组织了“10·5”政变，此次政变“被CIA内部视为成功开展和平秘密行动的蓝图”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gawker.com/new-head-of-cias-national-clandestine-service-outed-on-497210480 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-05-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140521032132/http://gawker.com/new-head-of-cias-national-clandestine-service-outed-on-497210480 |archive-date=2014-05-21 }} Berman, Taylor. Gawker: CIA's New Chief Spy Outed on Twitter - May 8, 2013</ref>

对南斯拉夫的制裁于2001年1月解除。<ref>{{cite journal|url= http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(01)05713-0/fulltext|title= Economic sanctions on Yugoslavia|access-date= 2016-05-02|doi= 10.1016/S0140-6736(01)05713-0|pmid= 11520550|volume= 358|issue= 9281|journal= The Lancet|page= 580|year= 2001|last1= Garfield|first1= Richard|archive-date= 2014-11-07|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141107190918/http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(01)05713-0/fulltext|dead-url= no}}</ref>布什政府领导的美国甚至在联合国制裁解除后几个月就否认向南斯拉夫提供任何援助，<ref>{{cite web|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/mar/25/opinion/op-42382|title=Bush Backtracks on Holding Kostunica's Feet to the Fire|work=latimes|access-date=2016-05-02|date=2001-03-25|archive-date=2018-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101085330/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/mar/25/opinion/op-42382|dead-url=no}}</ref>之后沃克斯拉夫·科什图尼察答应与海牙就斯洛博丹·米洛舍维奇的审判要求进行合作。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Marc Lacey |title=BUSH URGES LEADER'S TRIAL |url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2001-05-10/news/0105091041_1_slobodan-milosevic-war-crimes-yugoslavia |website=sun-sentinel |accessdate=2001-05-10 |archive-date=2013-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927113838/http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2001-05-10/news/0105091041_1_slobodan-milosevic-war-crimes-yugoslavia |dead-url=no }}</ref>
